parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and loss of control can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the throttle becomes stuck in the open position
the rear tire spins and loses grip
the vehicle slides or flips
and the driver loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Decelerate and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to decelerate and loss of control can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to decelerate
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the driver loses control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Issues and Parts Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall repair issues and parts unavailability can cause delays in repairing the vehicle, leaving it in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to perform the recall repair due to parts unavailability
the dealer charges the owner for parts that were never received
and the owner is left with an unsafe vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle speed control issues can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the throttle becomes stuck in the open position
and the driver loses control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame at the welds can cause the motorcycle to collapse, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The frame breaks in half at the welds
resulting in a clean break; the motorcycle collapses to the ground; the sub-frame cracks or breaks
affecting the passenger seat; the motorcycle is unsafe to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake master cylinder can cause the front brake to lock up without warning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, posing a serious risk to riders.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected front brake lock-up
loss of control
bike skidding or jumping
inability to stop the bike.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate response to the recall by the manufacturer can lead to riders being left without functional front brakes, putting them at risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Manufacturer refusing to perform the recall
refusal to provide necessary parts for repair
requiring riders to pay for towing to a dealer
lack of support for DIY repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of aftermarket levers with the recalled master cylinder can cause the front brake to malfunction, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Front brake lock-up
loss of control
bike skidding or jumping
inability to stop the bike.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch during winter and fall months can cause the motorcycle to become inoperable, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The clutch becomes inoperable
the clutch fails to engage or disengage properly
the motorcycle is unable to shift gears.
